{9010}{}{What was that all about? You okay?}
{10000}{}{[The young woman smiles and puts a cigarette to her lips. Her dark red lipstick stains the filter] Thanks to you, stranger. But oh don't mind me, I'm a big girl, I can handle my own problems. He's just another small kid playing in a big man's world. }
{10010}{}{It didn't look like nothing, anything I can help you with?}
{11000}{}{[She smiles and orders herself a drink] Could you be a doll, and fetch me a lighter? Pretty please, with cherries on top? }
{11010}{}{My pleasure. I'll be right back}
{11020}{}{We'll see. See ya.}
{12000}{}{[The day is dark, and full of rain. Hope is just finishing up one of her  performances when you walk up to greet her. The calm sounds of raindrops splashing keeps you at ease] Catch my last set? What did you think? The boys always tell me I'll make it to Reno some day.}
{12010}{}{It was beautiful, you sure know how to put on a show.}
{12020}{}{You remind me of the grandmother of all whores. The devil definitely got his dues tonight.}
{12030}{}{You belong somewhere you feel free. I don't think Reno is a place to start a new life. }
{12040}{}{Oh yeah, best ever. [Lie]}
{12050}{}{Show? You call that a show? When I was in the vault we had a thing called RADIO! Bitch! You can't sing. }
{13000}{}{You... you imbecile. You bloated idiot. You stupid fat-head you. This is what my dreams are made of!}
{14000}{}{[It rains on, loud than before] Thanks, stranger. Say, did you find me a lighter? A girl just can't be herself without a little... Flame. }
{14010}{}{Sure did, here. Consider it a gift... For the great performance.}
{14020}{}{No, I just came here for the show. I might come back.}
{15000}{}{[She stares you deep into the eyes, and says] You're too kind, }
{15010}{}{It's @pname@.}
{15020}{}{@pname@, just @pname@.}
{16000}{}{[The beautiful woman smiles, and gently shakes your hand] Charmed, I'm sure. @pname@ is such a pretty name, I'm Hope, the lounge singer. Been here for years, just singing my heart away, looking for the same thing we all are... Love, food, water... Bullets...}
{16010}{}{Aren't we all? So what was that argument all about anyways?}
{16020}{}{Things are tough all over, aren't they?}
{16030}{}{Anything I can help you with?}
{16040}{}{So you haven't lived a good life, eh? You better start talking, dame. }
{17000}{}{{The young woman takes a sip of her drink] ...Worse than you could ever know...}
{17010}{}{You know, that's good, because if you actually were as innocent as you pretend to be, we'd never get anywhere.}
{18000}{}{[She glances down at her drink. The sounds of rain keep on falling] When a man's partner is killed, he's supposed to do something about it. It doesn't make any difference what you thought of him. He was your partner and you're supposed to do something about it. And it happens when you're in the detective business. Well, when one of your organization gets killed, it's-it's bad business to let the killer get away with it, bad all around, bad for every detective everywhere.}
{18010}{}{Yeah, so? You kill someone?}
{19000}{}{[The youg woman's smile fades] No, but nobody exactly believes my story. They believed in the 200 dollars. I mean, I paid them more than if I had been telling the truth, and enough if I wasn't. }
{19010}{}{Who? The police?}
{20000}{}{[Hope smiles] Strange, how I never knew... I looked into his eyes, and I saw nothing. [She cries] Some kind of night, into the darkness, colours the eyes with what's not there.}
{20010}{}{[Put your hand on hers]}
{20020}{}{[Say nothing]}
{21000}{}{[The rain falls down like tears as Hope cries] You... you bungled it. You and your stupid attempt! }
{21010}{}{What are you talking about?}
{22000}{}{You've got to trust me, Mr. @pname@. Oh, I'm so alone and afraid. I've got nobody to help me if you won't help me. Be generous, Mr. @pname@. You're brave. You're strong. You can spare me some of that courage and strength surely. Help me, Mr. @pname@. I need help so badly. I've no right to ask you, I know I haven't, but I do ask you. Help me.}
{22010}{}{Don't be too sure I'm as crooked as I'm suppose to be.}
{22020}{}{You won't need much of anybody's help. You're good. It's chiefly your eyes, I think, and that throb you get in your voice when you say things like "Be generous, Mr. @pname@."}
{22030}{}{[smiling] Now you are dangerous.}
{23000}{}{[Hope backs away] I don't care what your secrets are. But I can't go ahead without more confidence in you than I've got now. You've got to convince me that you know what this is all about, that you aren't just fiddling around, hoping that it will all come out right in the end.}
{23010}{}{Clearly you've got some troubles, and judging by the fancy dress you're wearing, I reckon you've got some money to spend. You want to hire a real detective? }
{24000}{}{[Hope smiles] You always have a very smooth explanation ready.}
{24010}{}{What do you want me to do, learn to stutter?}
{25000}{}{[Hope takes your hand and leads you to her room] I couldn't be fonder of you if you were my own @sex@|son||daughter|. But, well, if you lose a kid, its possible to get another. There's only one Maltese Falcon. This is my home, but my husband is dead! And I'm afraid they suspect me to be the murderer!}
{25010}{}{Sounds tough, kiddo. }
{26000}{}{[The face she made at me was probably meant for a smile. Whatever it was, it beat me. I was afraid she'd do it again, so I surrendered] Won't you be my here? Care to play detective for a bit, and get to the bottom of things? I'll pay you 500 caps, double what I paid them. }
{26010}{}{Well, there's nothing certain either way. It depends. Maybe. }
{27000}{}{[Her face melts] You've been playing with me. Just pretending you care to trap me like this. You didn't care at all. You don't love me! Just... Just please think about it! Go over to the police station and snoop around. You're the only @sex@|man||girl| I've got! }
{27010}{}{[Walk away] }
